Page Title Suggestion:
ServiceNow Incident & Change Integration – Design Review (Incident Pulse + Enterprise Critical Products)
Labels / Categories: Architecture | Integration | ServiceNow | OCP | Spring-Boot
1. Objective
Provide a reliable, low-latency integration between the internal application (Spring Boot + Batch + MongoDB + Angular on OCP) and ServiceNow to fetch Incidents (every 15 minutes) and Changes (every hour), including impacted/affected services/CIs.
The data will power two key use cases:
Incident Pulse – Correlate network URL traceroute → IP-to-device mapping → device CPU/memory metrics with SNOW Incidents/Changes to triage latency/connectivity issues.
Enterprise Critical Products – Surface Incidents & Changes that impact applications, Flows, and Business Functions.
2. In-Scope / Out-of-Scope
In Scope
Polling of Incidents (incident table) and Changes (change_request table)
Fetching affected CIs and impacted services (via task_ci and task_cmdb_ci_service relationships)
Delta sync using sys_updated_on
Storage in MongoDB
REST endpoints for Angular front-end
Correlation hooks for Use Case 1 & 2
Out of Scope
Bi-directional updates back to ServiceNow
Full CMDB sync
Real-time webhooks (future phase)
ServiceNow OAuth token management UI
