5. Integration Approach (Detailed)
Authentication
Preferred: OAuth2 Client Credentials flow (ServiceNow supports it).
Store client-id, client-secret, token-endpoint in OCP Secrets / ConfigMap.
Use Spring Security OAuth2 Client.
Endpoints (Table API)
Incidents: GET /api/now/table/incident?sysparm_query=sys_updated_on>javascript:gs.dateGenerate('yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss')&sysparm_fields=number,short_description,priority,impact,urgency,category,state,assigned_to,cmdb_ci,sys_updated_on
Changes: GET /api/now/table/change_request?... (same fields + type, risk, impact)
Affected CIs: Query task_ci table where task=<incident_sys_id>
Impacted Services: Query task_cmdb_ci_service or use business_service reference
Delta Polling Logic
Store last_sync_timestamp per job type in MongoDB (or Redis).
Build encoded query: sys_updated_on>${last_sync} (use Instant in Java).
On success, update timestamp.
Batch Job Pseudocode
@Scheduled(cron = "0 */15 * * * *") // every 15 min
public void pollIncidents() {
    String query = buildDeltaQuery("incident", lastIncidentSync);
    List<IncidentDto> incidents = snowClient.getRecords("incident", query);
    incidents.forEach(incident -> {
        enrichWithAffectedCIsAndServices(incident);
        mongoRepo.upsert(incident);
    });
    updateLastSync("incident");
}
